history.content: Yes, according to the reserved seats information on classes.berkeley.edu for Data 100, the seats are reserved for those who have met the prereqs only. Starting this semester, CalCentral has the added functionality of enforcing prereqs for a class if the instructors want so, and this has been put in effect for Data 100 (possibly to give priority to the thousands of students taking data8 every year, and also because most of them would intend to declare the DS major).
